          <h3>Right to Limit Sensitive Personal Information (SPI) Use</h3>
          <p>
            The Company collects certain Personal Data (such as precise geolocation data in Usage Data) that may be considered Sensitive Personal Information. <strong>We only use this SPI as necessary to perform the services or provide the goods reasonably expected by an average consumer who requests those goods or services.</strong> We do not use Your SPI for purposes that require a Right to Limit under CPRA.
          </p>

          <h3>Non-Discrimination</h3>
          <p>
            We will not discriminate against You for exercising any of Your CCPA/CPRA rights.
          </p>

          <h3>Exercising Your CCPA/CPRA Rights</h3>
          <p>
            To exercise the rights described above, please submit a verifiable Consumer Request to Us by:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Email:</strong> dev@10botics.com</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section">
          <h2>Security of Your Personal Data</h2>
          <p>
            The security of Your Personal Data is important to Us, but remember that no method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. While We strive to use commercially reasonable means to protect Your Personal Data, We cannot guarantee its absolute security.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section">
          <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Our Service is designed to be used by children, and <strong>We collect Personal Data from children under the age of 13</strong>. This practice requires us to comply with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) in the United States and other similar international laws.
          </p>

          <h3>Parental Consent and Verification</h3>
          <p>
